{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, the best scaling factor will balance the tradeoff between weight dominance and weight uniformity.",
    "In this example, the scaling factor of",
    "appears near the knee of the two curves and provides a more representative distribution of weights as [0.18, 0.18, 0.18, 0.18, 0.28].",
    "That is, the weight of element X5 is now 1.6 times instead of 2.7 times the weight of the other elements.",
    "Intuition: The square root of the dimension of a vector is a common choice when scaling down the magnitude to improve the stability of matrix multiplications."
  ]
}